# Document Started on 03/26/2024
# Version 0.1

# Step-by-Step Installation Commands of VMware Workstation 12 on CentOS 7

# Download VMware Workstation 12:
# Visit the VMware website and download VMware Workstation 12 for Linux.
# Install Required Dependencies:
# Ensure your CentOS 7 system is up to date
sudo yum update

# Install development tools and kernel headers
sudo yum install gcc kernel-devel

# Make the Installer Executable & save it user home directory

# Make the installer executable
chmod +x VMware-Workstation-Full-12.x.x-xxxxxxx.x86_64.bundle

# Run the Installer:
# Execute the installer with root privileges
sudo ./VMware-Workstation-Full-12.x.x-xxxxxxx.x86_64.bundle


# Follow the Installation Wizard:
# The installer will guide you through the installation process.
# Accept the license agreement.

# Start VMware Workstation
# Launch VMware Workstation from the applications menu or terminal
# Verify Installation
# Open VMware Workstation and ensure it starts without errors.

# Remember to replace 12.x.x-xxxxxxx with the specific version you downloaded

